						<summary>

						<p>On the south base, central shrine, Kailāśanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 15: 986 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> for a flywhisk with a golden handle by Pañchavan-Mahādēviyār, the queen of Parakēsarivarman <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> śrī Uttama-chōḷa, to god Śrī Kailāsamuḍaiya-mahādēvar at śrī Sembiyanmahadēvi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam</hi> in Aḷa-nāḍu on the southern bank (of the river Kāvēri) created by the dowager queen Śrī Parāntakaṉ-mādēvaḍigaḷ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śrī Sembiyanmahādēviyār, the mother of Kaṇḍan Madhurāntakadēvar <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> śrī Uttama-chōḻadēvar.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 382.</p>						

						</summary>
